import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['size'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Size')
    plt.axvline(data['size'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['size'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Size')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of size in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Group by parent and calculate the average size
    avg_size_by_parent = data.groupby('parent')['size'].mean().reset_index()

    # Create a bar chart
    ax = avg_size_by_parent.plot.bar(x='parent', y='size', legend=False)
    
    # Set the title and labels
    plt.title('What is the average size of items in each parent category?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Parent Category')
    plt.ylabel('Average Size')
    
    # Rotate x-axis labels for better readability
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    data.boxplot(column='size', by='parent', ax=ax)
    plt.title('What is the size distribution of items in each parent category?')
    plt.xlabel('Parent Category')
    plt.ylabel('Size')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Parent Categories', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    max_sizes = data.groupby('parent')['size'].max()
    max_sizes.plot(kind='bar', color='blue', legend=True)
    plt.title('What is the largest item in each parent category?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Parent Category')
    plt.ylabel('Max Size')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    min_sizes = data.groupby('parent')['size'].min().reset_index()
    ax = min_sizes.plot.bar(x='parent', y='size', legend=False)
    plt.title('What is the smallest item in each parent category?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Parent Category')
    plt.ylabel('Min Size')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.axhline(min_sizes['size'].min(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Min: {min_sizes['size'].min():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
